$ SQL Server: INFORMATION_SCHEMA
@ INFORMATION_SCHEMA

INFORMATION_SCHEMA is the ANSI way do query meta data about objects in SQL databases. SQL server implements them as
views that (usually?) access tables in the → development/databases/SQL-Server/administration/schemas/sys[sys schema].

{ Select all views in INFORMATION_SCHEMA

  The following query allows to find all views in the INFORMATION_SCHEMA schema:
  gh|about-MSSQL|/administration/schemas/INFORMATION_SCHEMA/select-views.sql||

  It returns:
    • CHECK_CONSTRAINTS
    • COLUMN_DOMAIN_USAGE
    • COLUMN_PRIVILEGES
    • → development/databases/SQL-Server/administration/schemas/INFORMATION_SCHEMA/columns[COLUMNS]
    • CONSTRAINT_COLUMN_USAGE
    • CONSTRAINT_TABLE_USAGE
    • DOMAIN_CONSTRAINTS
    • DOMAINS
    • KEY_COLUMN_USAGE
    • PARAMETERS
    • REFERENTIAL_CONSTRAINTS
    • ROUTINE_COLUMNS
    • ROUTINES
    • SCHEMATA
    • SEQUENCES
    • TABLE_CONSTRAINTS
    • TABLE_PRIVILEGES
    • TABLES
    • VIEW_COLUMN_USAGE
    • VIEW_TABLE_USAGE
    • VIEWS



}

sa:

 [columns]

 → development/databases/SQL-Server/administration/schemas

